Description: The company developed 1.7 million square feet of commercial retail and office space from 1994 through 2008 when the collapse occurred.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: The company developed 1.7 million square feet of commercial retail and office space from 1994 through 2008 when the collapse occurred in the financial and real estate market place. In addition the company developed multiple subdivisions in Northwest Arkansas. When money tightened up there was little room to negotiate with banks and most developers along with the company lost most if not all of their holdings.     The plan I want to put into place would not allow that to happen because all construction and land would be done with cash from investors. Using small tracts of land that would allow up to 100 homes would give us savings in scale and timing. The target market would be for senior citizens wanting to downsize but not wanting to forfeit their luxury living home comforts. Houses would all be one level and be from 3,000 square feet to 3,500 square feet. Each unit would have the finest appliances, large closets for the master suite and a bathroom fit for kings. It would have real wood floors and everything would be directed toward ease of care and maintenance. There would be a POA that would take care of mowing, landscape, snow removal and maintenance of a walking trail, swimming pool and common area recreation.     Ten houses would be started every two months and the schedule would be to complete each ten house units in five months. In 29 months the entire project could be built and sold and investors could make up to a 28% annual return on their investment. I have a business plan and pro forma sheets that show timeline of money needed and of return potential for the investors.

Biologists run these dolphin tours as part of their research on these beloved aquatic animals, so you know this will be an interesting trip. Passengers will be able to see how researchers with the Outer Banks Center for Dolphin Research, a nonprofit organization, conduct their research and hear about some of the discoveries from more than a decade of studies and monitoring. Some of the hundreds of Atlantic bottlenose dolphins in the area show up so frequently they’ve even been given names, like “Rake,” “Scarlet,” and “Onion.” Onion was first identified in Beaufort, North Carolina almost 20 years ago, and he has been sighted there almost every winter since. It has been discovered that Nags Head is his summer home, along with an extensive family of more than 100 members. In his early years, Onion had an unfortunate encounter with a boat propeller and his damaged fin has made him one of the most easily recognized dolphins around. Click on the title below to see a great article in the July 2016 My Outer Banks Home by Meg Puckett entitled Fins Up! … A day on the water with Outer Banks Center for Dolphin Research.

Because of the fragmented nature of the market in its current state, the threat from competitors is not necessarily a negative reality, and additional competitors in the market help increase awareness and drive overall sales, leading to more acquisitions and industry consolidation. Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Flexamat, a tied concrete block mat, is used to control erosion in swales, ditches, slopes, shoreline protection, or any area where soil sediment can be moved by water runoff.   Flexamat consists of concrete shapes, rectangular or round, that are tied together with high strength geogrid. This product results in the geogrid and the concrete becoming a high strength flexible hard armor against erosion. Flexamat enables vegetation to become established while remaining a permanent armor against future erosion. Eventually, vegetation will cover the entire mat.   Flexamat comes in rolls and is available in widths of 5.5', 8', 10', and 16'. These rolls are available in various lengths. The roll design makes installation very efficient. The application area should be graded so that the Flexamat has direct contact with the subgrade. It should also be seeded priot to the Flexamat installation. A smooth bucket on the excavator is used to until the mat into place.
